   Series of absorbing documentaries exploring remarkable stories of human 
   experience from all over the world. Thirteen-year-old Marlie Casseus is 
   one of the bravest girls in the world. A terrible disease is killing her, 
   destroying her face from the inside, as a seven-kilo growth is closing 
   her throat and making breathing difficult. This documentary follows 
   Marlie as she undergoes high-risk surgery that claims a place in 
   medical history.
